  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team lead",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Discretization error achieved Gradation 4 against a Gradation 3 requirement, providing additional margin. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (N=2000) confirms that the 95th-percentile NIH prediction remains 18% below the clinical acceptance threshold across the COU operating envelope. Independent two-person review of simulation setup found no use errors. Model form uncertainty, assessed by comparison against an alternative hemolysis model, contributes less than 12% spread in NIH — within the accepted uncertainty budget. Validation against five FDA generic pump experimental operating points yields mean absolute error of 8.3%, well within the ±15% acceptance criterion. The provenance chain from foundational experimental data through UQ to the decision record is complete and traceable. On the basis of this structured evidence, the CFD hemolysis prediction model is judged credible for the COU2 intended use and the decision is Accepted.",
